### 3D-R3 — GLTF / MODEL OPTIMISATION
- Use **Draco compression** on all GLTF models
- Max **5 MB per model** — no exceptions
- Use `GLTFLoader` + `DRACOLoader` together:
```js
import { DRACOLoader } from 'three/examples/jsm/loaders/DRACOLoader';
import { GLTFLoader }  from 'three/examples/jsm/loaders/GLTFLoader';

const dracoLoader = new DRACOLoader();
dracoLoader.setDecoderPath('/draco/');

const loader = new GLTFLoader();
loader.setDRACOLoader(dracoLoader);
```

---

### 3D-R4 — MOBILE GPU RULE
Disable postprocessing effects (bloom, SSAO, motion blur, etc.) on screens narrower than 768px:
```js
const isMobile = window.innerWidth < 768;

if (!isMobile) {
  composer.addPass(bloomPass);
  composer.addPass(ssaoPass);
}
```
Postprocessing on mobile = dropped frames, overheating, bad UX.

---

### 3D-R5 — VERCEL.JSON IS MANDATORY
For any React / React Three Fiber project, `vercel.json` MUST exist:
```json
{ "rewrites": [{ "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }] }
```
(Repeated from R7 — intentional. This is the #1 forgotten step in 3D projects.)

